data.chText: （尤指未通过公正选举的）统治方式，统治制度，政权，政体
data.enText: a method or system of government, especially one that has not been elected in a fair way

data.chText: 法西斯、极权主义、军事等政权
压迫民众的 / 残暴的政权

data.enText: a method or system of organizing or managing sth

data.chText: 我们的税收管理体制是欧洲最受欢迎的税收体制之一。
data.enText: Our tax regime is one of the most favourable in Europe.

means: (尤指未通过公正选举的)统治方式

tr: (medicine) a systematic plan for therapy (often including diet)
the organization that is the governing authority of a political unit
example: the matter was referred to higher authorities

value.def: If you refer to a government or system of running a country as a regime, you are critical of it because you think it is not democratic and uses unacceptable methods.

example.ex: ...the collapse of the Fascist regime at the end of the war...
example.tran: 在战争末期法西斯政权的倒台

example.ex: Pujol was imprisoned and tortured under the Franco regime.
example.tran: 普约尔在佛朗哥政权统治时期受到了监禁和折磨。

value.tran: 政权，政体（指非民主且统治手段不被认可的政府或政权体系）

value.def: A regime is the way that something such as an institution, company, or economy is run, especially when it involves tough or severe action.

example.ex: The authorities moved him to the less rigid regime of an open prison.
example.tran: 当局把他转到一个管制不那么严格的开放式监狱。

example.ex: ...a drastic regime of economic reform and financial discipline.
example.tran: 雷厉风行的经济改革和财经纪律

value.tran: （机构、公司、经济等的）管理制度，组织方法

value.def: A regime is a set of rules about food, exercise, or beauty that some people follow in order to stay healthy or attractive.

example.ex: He has a new fitness regime to strengthen his back.
example.tran: 他有一个增强背部力量的新健身计划。
